pageContext.description: Rectangular mouth, base surrounded by a cornice like moulding on which is marked a bead; 3 ribs converge on each face, starting from the cornice; the pattern is smaller on one face than on the other. the seam of casting is worked into a sharp ridge on either side. Loop is injured and stands on two horizontal ridges.
pageContext.patina: Dark brown, speckled with turquoise blue corroded pits.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology + Ethnology, Cambridge,Foster Bequest No. 48 (No. 51 is correct in Catalogue),Prehistoric Bronzes No. 101 (Catalogue is lost.),Borlase Collection
